activitySummary: The user is engaged in a Zoom meeting, as indicated by the active Zoom application on the left half of the screen. The meeting involves two participants, Tristan Muniz and Isaac Squires, as shown in the video conference layout. The Zoom interface displays various controls such as Mute, Stop Video, Participants, Chat, Share Screen, Summary, Reactions, Apps, Notes, and a Leave button. This suggests that the user is actively participating in a video conference, possibly discussing project-related matters or collaborating with team members.

On the right half of the screen, Visual Studio Code is open but not active. The code editor displays a file named 'DamageController.cs' within the 'CombatScripts\Runtime' directory. The code snippet visible involves a method 'OnAttributeChanged' that handles attribute change events. The method includes logic to check if an attribute value is less than zero, setting a flag '_isDeath' to true, and publishing a combat entity state change event if certain conditions are met. This indicates that the user is working on backend code related to game character attributes and state changes.
